ch.epfl.biop.operetta

Class OperettaManager.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.epfl.biop.operetta.OperettaManager.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    OperettaManager

    public static class OperettaManager.Builder
extends Object
    This Builder class handles creating OperettaManager objects for you

    If you're curious about the Builder Pattern, you can read Joshua Bloch's excellent Effective Java Book

    Use When creating a new OperettaManager object, call the Builder, add all the options and then call the build() method 

     * 
 * OperettaManager opm = new OperettaManager.Builder()
 									.setId( id )
 									.setSaveFolder( save_dir )
 								//  Other options here
 									.build();
 * 
 *

    • Method Detail

      • flipHorizontal

        public OperettaManager.Builder flipHorizontal(boolean isFlip)
        Flip the individual tiles Horizontally. This information is encoded by PerkinElmer in a transformation matrix But we do not have access to it from Bioformats and Bioformats only uses it for positioning So flips in the coordinates (-1 in the matrix) are not actually handled.
        Parameters:
        isFlip - is the data flipped Horizontally
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • flipVertical

        public OperettaManager.Builder flipVertical(boolean isFlip)
        Flip the individual tiles Vertically. This information is encoded by PerkinElmer in a transformation matrix But we do not have access to it from Bioformats and Bioformats only uses it for positioning So flips in the coordinates (-1 in the matrix) are not actually handled.
        Parameters:
        isFlip - is the data flipped Vertically
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • setProjectionMethod

        public OperettaManager.Builder setProjectionMethod(String method)
        The projection method to use
        Parameters:
        method - String that matches one of the strings in the ZProjector
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • setNormalization

        public OperettaManager.Builder setNormalization(int min,
                                                int max)
        Sets the values for min-max normalization In the case of digital phase images, these are in 32-bits and ImageJ cannot mix 32-bit images with 16-bit images (the standard Operetta bit depth). So we set the min and max display range that will be converted to 0-65535
        Parameters:
        min - value of the digital phase image that will be set to 0
        max - value of the digital phase image that will be set to 65535
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • setId

        public OperettaManager.Builder setId(File id)
        This sets the id (the path to the image file), as per Bioformat's definition In the case of Operetta Data, the ID is the 'Index.idx.xml' file you get when you export it. This is usually provided as an absolute path
        Parameters:
        id - the full path of 'Index.idx.xml', in String format
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • reader

        public OperettaManager.Builder reader(IFormatReader reader)
        As an alternative to using an id, when the dataset is big, one can provide am already existing reader, which is a way to optimise the opening of a dataset
        Parameters:
        reader - the reader
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • setRange

        public OperettaManager.Builder setRange(HyperRange range)
        Can provide a range (Channels, Slices and Timepoints) to use for export. If none are provided, will export the full range of the data
        Parameters:
        range - the HyperRange object, see corresponding class
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • setSaveFolder

        public OperettaManager.Builder setSaveFolder(File save_folder)
        Provides the save folder to which data will be exported to
        Parameters:
        save_folder - the folder. If not created, this method will try to create it.
        Returns:
        a Builder object, to continue building parameters

      • coordinatesCorrectionFactor

      • build

        public OperettaManager build()
        The build method handles creating an OperettaManager object from all the settings that were provided. This is done so that everything, like the HyperRange that is defined is valid.
        Returns:
        the instance to the OperettaManager.
